00:12:47,690 --> 00:12:49,160
晚春
Late spring,

183
00:12:49,940 --> 00:12:51,080
太阳谷
Sun Valley.

184
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:56,070
你一点没变
You look exactly the same.

185
00:12:56,070 --> 00:12:58,450
城市催人老
Well, it's cities that age you,

186
00:12:58,450 --> 00:12:59,990
我总跟人那么说
it's what I tell everyone.

187
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,120
希望你不介意
I hope you don't mind

188
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:06,060
跟几位我们最好的朋友打招呼
saying hello to a few of our closest friends.

189
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:10,370
他们就是来喝杯鸡尾酒
They're just here for a cocktail before the--

190
00:13:10,370 --> 00:13:13,260
等着太阳落山后  其余的客人到来
the sun goes down and the rest of the party shows up.

191
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:17,100
我妹妹的烟火秀算是成了个传统了
My sister's fireworks show have become a bit of a tradition.

192
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,730
别担心  他们会保密的
Don't worry. They know how to be discreet.

193
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:31,810
斯考特刚收购了奈克西斯安保
Scotty here just got his hands on Nexis Security.

194
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:34,130
听说你还要就此事跟副总统谈
I heard you are speaking to the vice president about this.

195
00:13:34,130 --> 00:13:36,140
就是一家维和公司
It's a company of peacekeepers, mostly.

196
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:39,250
有构建国际合作的大潜力
Oh, tremendous potential to create global partnerships.

197
00:13:39,250 --> 00:13:40,630
是你丈夫帮我谈妥了协议
Your husband helped me secure the deal.

198
00:13:40,630 --> 00:13:42,630
我本想拉他进董事会的
I wanted to bring him onto the Board.

199
00:13:43,370 --> 00:13:44,460
比尔还说...
Bill was saying...

200
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:45,890
是啊  我还说呢
Yes, I was just saying.

201
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:47,560
他们为什么要在
Why in the world do they play

202
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:50,890
烟火秀上演奏《1812序曲》
the "1812 Overture" at a fireworks show?

203
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:53,420
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}由柴科夫斯基创作
纪念1812年俄国人民击退拿破仑大军的入侵
作品以曲中的炮火声闻名  一些演出中还会真用大炮

204
00:13:50,890 --> 00:13:53,420
那可是彻头彻尾的俄国曲子
It's Russian, for Chrissakes, in every sense.

205
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,400
这是塔比莎
This is Tabitha.

206
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:58,560
彼得斯  我知道
Peters, I know.

207
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:00,500
弗兰克
Frank...

208
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,650
-他今天本来也会到的吧  -是啊
- Wasn't he planning to be here today? - He was.

209
00:14:03,650 --> 00:14:05,520
你肯定很想他
You must miss him terribly.

210
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:09,420
我曾多次跟他进行过长时间的激烈对话
I had some long and hard-fought conversations with him.

211
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:12,700
他本想帮我解决内华达州那边
He was going to help me resolve this AFL-CIO thing

212
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,660
旷日持久的劳联-产联的问题
that's been going on forever out in Nevada,

213
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:16,450
当然了  是在你的帮助下
with your help, of course.

214
00:14:16,450 --> 00:14:19,110
工会如果阻挡创新
When the union stands in the way of innovation,

215
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:21,200
就是自寻死路
it's sentencing itself to death.

216
00:14:22,610 --> 00:14:25,610
我很欣赏你坚持与党派站在一起
I do admire the way you hang on to your party.

217
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:26,730
如此忠诚
Your loyalty.

218
00:14:27,990 --> 00:14:30,090
这是真的吗  据说南茜·盖拉格中将
Did I hear that Lieutenant General Nancy Gallagher

219
00:14:30,090 --> 00:14:32,280
今天稍后会与你一同露面
will be appearing with you later today?

220
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:38,470
我认为她能是个好候选人
I think she'd make an excellent candidate,

221
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,990
如果她决定竞选的话
if she decides to run, of course.

222
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:43,230
她绝对会的
Oh, she's going to run.

223
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:50,820
总统日程很紧
The president is on a tight schedule.

224
00:14:58,030 --> 00:14:59,120
失陪
Excuse me.

225
00:15:16,050 --> 00:15:18,060
这真令人没想到
Well, this is a surprise.

226
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,870
你知道中西部的人不喜欢意料之外的事
You know how Midwesterners feel about those.

227
00:15:21,870 --> 00:15:25,160
别听他的  你也该出来了
Oh, don't listen to him. It's about time you came out.

228
00:15:25,490 --> 00:15:27,810
我们似乎有事要谈
Seems we have some things to discuss.

229
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:28,820
是啊
Yeah.

230
00:15:28,990 --> 00:15:32,120
就这场特别选举来说  克莱尔
Well, as far as this special election is concerned, Claire,

231
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:36,360
你要知道即将退休的盖拉格女士
you need to know that the soon-to-be-retiring Miss Gallagher

232
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:37,590
是绝对不行的
is out of question.

233
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:40,210
我很高兴我们都喜欢
And I'm happy to see we're both fans

234
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:42,670
《独立宣言》
of the Declaration of Independence,

235
00:15:42,670 --> 00:15:44,190
天赋人权什么的
unalienable rights and all that.

236
00:15:44,190 --> 00:15:46,680
但你待会儿要发表的演讲里写着...
But it says down here in the speech you're gonna give later--

237
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,850
我支持盖拉格女士
Miss Gallagher has my support.

238
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,960
我相信马克表达了我们的担忧
I believe Mark conveyed our concerns.

239
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:55,100
希望他也表达了我的
And communicated mine, I hope.

240
00:15:55,490 --> 00:15:58,670
她褪去军装就是个支持大政府的民主党
She's a tax and spend Democrat underneath that uniform.

241
00:15:58,670 --> 00:16:01,320
-是简历卓越的爱国者  -克莱尔
- A patriot with a pristine resume. - Claire.

242
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:04,210
而且高调反对让私人承包商
Who is very vocal about keeping private contractors

243
00:16:04,210 --> 00:16:06,600
-插手美军行动  -就算作为协商筹码
- away from US military operations. - Even as a negotiating point,

244
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,760
也有比她强的
you can do better than her.

245
00:16:07,770 --> 00:16:10,070
我厌倦了你的拖延  总统女士
And I am tired of these delays, Madam President.

246
00:16:10,070 --> 00:16:11,980
你该说到做到了
It is time for you to deliver.

247
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:17,460
-你丈夫和我有协议的  -弗兰西斯死了
- Your husband and I had an agreement. - Francis is dead.

248
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:20,030
-我们得到了承诺  -不是我给的
- Promises were made. - Not by me.

249
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:26,440
就像你一样  我也想自己谈协议
Just like you, I like to negotiate my own agreements.

250
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:27,610
别搞错了
And make no mistake about it,

251
00:16:27,610 --> 00:16:29,990
中将并不是个例外
the lieutenant general is not an anomaly.

252
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:32,590
我知道  我看到了你的中期选举候选人
I know that. I've seen your list of candidates for the midterms--

253
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:33,720
是啊  大都是女人
Yes, mostly women.

254
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,890
我才不管他们是男是女
I don't care what sex they are.

255
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:38,640
另外  没人比我更喜欢女人了
And for the record, nobody loves women more than me.

256
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:41,010
但你的候选人名单  会拖垮这个国家
But this slate of yours, it will bankrupt the country.

257
00:16:41,010 --> 00:16:44,120
会让我们倒退一代  会完全...
They will set us back a generation. They will completely--

258
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:47,650
支持我  和我的立场
Support me and what I stand for.

259
00:16:47,650 --> 00:16:48,590
那是什么
And what is that?

260
00:16:48,590 --> 00:16:50,440
-得了  比尔  -不  你说啊
- Oh, come on, Bill. - No, no. Tell me.

261
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,080
我想听听  你的使命是什么
I wanna know. What's your mission?

262
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,240
-我想知道你的纲领是什么  -得了
- I wanna know what your platform is. - Oh, please.

263
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,490
我知道你想一下肃清华府
I know you'd like to drown DC all at once.

264
00:16:56,490 --> 00:16:59,270
但我这就告诉你  我不会允许的
But I'm gonna tell you right now, I cannot let that happen.

265
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:00,600
我依然相信政府
I still believe in government

266
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:04,630
相信它有能力改善其公民的日常生活
and its ability to make the everyday lives of its citizens better.

267
00:17:04,630 --> 00:17:06,370
-嗯  -你不想支持我的候选人
- Yeah. - You don't wanna support my slate,

268
00:17:06,370 --> 00:17:07,360
好啊
that's fine.

269
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:11,450
-克莱尔  -我只要求你别碍事
- Claire... - All I ask is stay out of the way.

270
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:17,050
你桌上有一份法案
There's a bill sitting on your desk.

271
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:20,550
这份法案耗时数年
A bill that took years...

272
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:23,350
耗费财力才获得通过
and money to get passed.

273
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:24,910
你签署了
You sign that,

274
00:17:25,570 --> 00:17:28,010
我就知道我在白宫里有朋友
and I know I got a friend in the White House.

275
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:30,420
如果你不签
If not...

276
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,960
-那我就没有  -够了
- Then I don't. - Enough.

277
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,500
有她在  你是不会有好果子吃的
Nothing good happens to you when she's around.

278
00:17:39,510 --> 00:17:40,480
相信我
Nothing.

279
00:17:41,350 --> 00:17:43,750
你为什么赞助了弗兰西斯
Why did you come out for Francis?

280
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,120
他的基金会
For his foundation?

281
00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:47,400
我没觉得你真喜欢过他
I don't think you ever really liked him.

282
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:51,750
可能从未尊重过他  为什么现在支持他
Probably never respected him. Why back him now?

283
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:55,160
因为他把你给了我们
Because he gave us you.

284
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:01,620
告诉我们的朋友们  我会赶上下来看烟火的
Tell our friends I'll be back down in time for the fireworks.

285
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:13,410
你要知道  我一直喜欢弗兰克
Just so you know, I always liked Frank.

286
00:18:15,690 --> 00:18:17,020
喜欢他的绝望
His desperation.

287
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,020
很遗憾你不能留下
I'm sorry you can't stay.

288
00:18:23,670 --> 00:18:26,130
我很喜欢组织我们的烟火秀
I do enjoy curating our little show.

289
00:18:27,350 --> 00:18:30,530
我出行时收集了各种烟火弹
I collect a variety of fireworks shells as I travel.

290
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:32,810
意大利  西班牙  中国
Italy, Spain, China.

291
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:36,940
你知道最难做的色彩是什么吗
Do you know what the hardest color to make is?

292
00:18:39,170 --> 00:18:41,320
-红色吗  -不  红色很简单
- Red? - No, red's easy.

293
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:42,900
白色也很简单
White's easy.

294
00:18:44,060 --> 00:18:45,180
是蓝色
It's blue.

295
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:48,810
铜和温度的化学调剂很难弄
Very tricky chemistry involving copper and heat.

296
00:18:48,810 --> 00:18:51,570
真正的亮蓝色是非常不好做的
A truly bright blue is extremely elusive.

297
00:18:53,740 --> 00:18:56,640
不管弗兰西斯承诺了什么  做了什么
Whatever Francis promised or did...

298
00:18:57,570 --> 00:18:59,060
都跟他一起入土了
is buried with him.

299
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,190
我知道
No, I know.

300
00:19:02,830 --> 00:19:04,880
我们都得对他放手
We all need to let him go.

301
00:19:05,910 --> 00:19:08,170
从头做起
Start from some kind of scratch.

302
00:19:10,770 --> 00:19:12,360
但你肯定很难安吧
Though it must haunt you,

303
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:16,060
他就在床上你身旁长眠不起
the fact that he died next to you in bed.

304
00:19:23,450 --> 00:19:24,490
亲爱的
Hon...

305
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,380
耐心点
be patient.

306
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:34,670
你是说  她不喜欢这名字吗
Are you saying, she doesn't like the name?

307
00:19:34,670 --> 00:19:35,810
我觉得她认为名字不够完整
I think she finds it incomplete.

308
00:19:35,810 --> 00:19:37,500
《综合安全法案》有什么不好
What's wrong with the Comprehensive Safety Act?

309
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,890
那《综合化学安全法案》呢
Comprehensive Chemical Safety Act?

310
00:19:38,890 --> 00:19:41,010
也可以再回去用《精简安全法案》
Or we could go back to the Smarter Safety Act.

311
00:19:41,010 --> 00:19:42,470
她会更喜欢"精简"吗
Would she like "smarter" better?

312
00:19:42,470 --> 00:19:44,090
不行  得有个好缩写
No, we need a good acronym.

313
00:19:44,130 --> 00:19:45,400
副总统先生
Mr. Vice President?

314
00:19:46,050 --> 00:19:47,020
马克
Mark?

315
00:19:48,710 --> 00:19:49,870
嗯  是啊
Yeah. Agreed.

316
00:19:50,070 --> 00:19:53,790
我们还曾考虑过《不安全监管废止法案》
At one point, we talked about the Repeal Unsafe Regulation Act.

317
00:19:53,790 --> 00:19:55,760
如果能再加个L开头的就是"农村"了
That's RURAL if we come up with an L.

318
00:19:55,770 --> 00:19:56,840
立法吗
Legislation?

319
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:58,150
那跟其他的凑不到一起去
That doesn't make sense with the rest of it.

320
00:19:58,150 --> 00:20:00,780
"农村"这词不好念  "安全"更好
"RURAL" is too hard to say. "SAFE" is good.

321
00:20:00,780 --> 00:20:02,480
安全  未来
Safety. Future.

322
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:07,130
-"未来"好  -联邦综合有毒危险物...
- I like "FUTURE." - Federal Universal Toxic and Unsafe...

323
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:09,190
-去监管法案  -好
- Regulation Eradication. - Okay.

324
00:20:09,790 --> 00:20:11,920
-那就《未来法案》了  -可以
- The FUTURE Act. - That could work.

325
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:13,980
可以问一下  副总统先生
May I ask, Mr. Vice President,

326
00:20:13,980 --> 00:20:17,020
除了名字她还有其他疑虑吗
does her hesitation go beyond the name?

327
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:20,760
她会想通的  我猜...
She'll come around. I'm guessing...

328
00:20:21,570 --> 00:20:22,820
到今天晚上吧
by the end of the day.

329
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:24,590
因为不管是什么名字
Because in one form or another,

330
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:25,630
这份法案已经在她桌上放了...
this bill has been on her desk since--

331
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:26,940
她会签的  亨利
She'll sign it, Henry.

332
00:20:29,330 --> 00:20:30,250
比尔
Bill.

333
00:20:34,180 --> 00:20:35,400
你要我做什么
What do you want me to do?

334
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,430
把她从自己的军事基地拽回来吗
Yank her from her own military base?

335
00:20:41,480 --> 00:20:45,420
在人类大事件的过程中  当一个人
When, in the course of human events, it becomes necessary

336
00:20:45,710 --> 00:20:48,410
有必要解除将他们与另一个人
for one people to dissolve the political bands

337
00:20:48,410 --> 00:20:50,680
联系在一起的政治纽带时
which have connected them with another,

338
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,720
你得当机立断
you just have to do it.

339
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:55,130
切断关系
Sever the relationship.

340
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:58,400
我们国家的立国文献
Our nation's founding document,

341
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,410
《独立宣言》
the Declaration of Independence--

342
00:21:00,410 --> 00:21:02,140
美国的独立
America's independence--

343
00:21:02,140 --> 00:21:05,380
是经过艰苦斗争赢来的
was hard-fought and hard-won.

344
00:21:05,380 --> 00:21:06,660
你还在听吗
Are you still there?

345
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:10,980
我们的国父构想了一个自由国度
Our Founding Fathers imagined a nation that was free.

346
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:13,080
摆脱专制
Free from despotism.

347
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:15,750
摆脱暴政
Free from absolute tyranny.

348
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:18,590
摆脱国王压迫
Free from an oppressive king.

349
00:21:18,700 --> 00:21:20,040
你想弗兰西斯了吗
Do you miss Francis?

350
00:21:20,050 --> 00:21:22,400
暴君有多种多样
Tyrants come in many forms.

351
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:24,720
从美国政治寡头
From the American oligarchs

352
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:27,740
企图改变社会根本
trying to change the very fabric of our society,

353
00:21:28,510 --> 00:21:31,020
到在海外叫嚣的独裁者
to autocrats threatening from abroad.

354
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:37,010
我们每个人都要维护我们的命运
Now, each one of us has to defend our destiny.

355
00:21:37,790 --> 00:21:39,350
在我看来
And as I see it,

356
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:44,100
抵抗暴政是战争的唯一合理理由
the fight against tyranny is the only justification for war.

357
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:49,790
我作为总统的头一百天很艰难
My first 100 days as president have been difficult.

358
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,560
我失去了丈夫
I lost my husband.

359
00:21:53,660 --> 00:21:56,340
我们本来正要庆祝结婚30周年
We were about to celebrate 30 years together.

360
00:21:57,230 --> 00:21:59,250
但我了解他的心愿
But I know what he would want.

361
00:21:59,770 --> 00:22:02,750
他会希望我停止哀伤  继续生活
For me to stop mourning and carry on.

362
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:07,160
在南茜·盖拉格中将这样的女性的帮助下
With the help of women like Lieutenant General Nancy Gallagher,

363
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:09,600
我的任期将充满实干
my presidency will not rest.

364
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:12,490
南茜深深激励了我
Nancy has been an inspiration to me.

365
00:22:12,910 --> 00:22:14,750
她是不倦的勇士
A tireless warrior.

366
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,770
我向她也向你们保证
I promise her and all of you

367
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:18,770
我会为我们的民主国家
that I will work on behalf of the rights

368
00:22:18,770 --> 00:22:22,900
这241年间所赢得的权利和自由而奋斗
and freedoms earned over the last 241 years of our democracy.

369
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,560
当我看着今天
As I look into the eyes

370
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:29,520
站在我面前的这些勇敢战士们的眼睛
of you brave soldiers standing before me today...

371
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:30,320
是这样的
Here's the thing.

372
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,970
我此刻无比骄傲
I'm feeling so proud right now.

373
00:22:32,970 --> 00:22:35,210
为做你们的三军统帅骄傲
Proud to be your Commander-in-Chief.

374
00:22:35,210 --> 00:22:37,720
不管弗兰西斯这五年来对你们说了什么
Whatever Francis told you the last five years,

375
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,430
一个字都别信
don't believe a word of it.

376
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:42,710
我们国家已经241岁了  朋友们
Our country is 241 years old, my friends.

377
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:45,640
我们祝这个伟大国家生日快乐吧
Let's wish this great nation a happy birthday.

378
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:46,940
跟我一起说
Say it with me.

379
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:49,310
生日快乐  美国
Happy birthday, America!

380
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:52,300
生日快乐  美国
Happy Birthday, America!

381
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,660
我们的情况会有所不同
It's going to be different for you and me.

382
00:22:53,660 --> 00:22:54,780
再来一次
One more time.

383
00:22:54,990 --> 00:22:56,370
我要对你说实话
I'm going to tell you the truth.

384
00:22:56,380 --> 00:22:58,650
生日快乐  美国
Happy Birthday, America.

385
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:02,010
-谢谢你的服役  -谢谢
- Thank you for your service. - Thank you.

386
00:23:02,950 --> 00:23:04,500
谢谢你的服役
Thank you for your service.

387
00:23:05,490 --> 00:23:07,540
-谢谢你的服役  -谢谢
- Thank you for your service. - Thank you.

388
00:23:09,290 --> 00:23:12,440
我希望你们知道我有多高兴能来见见
I want you to know how wonderful it is to be here and meet

389
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:14,030
你们这些新兵
all of you new recruits.

390
00:23:14,260 --> 00:23:15,480
谢谢你
So, thank you.

391
00:23:15,610 --> 00:23:16,940
谢谢你的服役
Thank you for your service.

392
00:23:16,940 --> 00:23:18,630
-谢谢  -谢谢  女士
- Thank you. - Thank you, ma'am.

393
00:23:19,010 --> 00:23:21,460
谢谢你的服役  你是哪来的  二等兵
Thank you for your service. Where are you from, private?

394
00:23:21,460 --> 00:23:23,050
卡拉马祖  总统先生
Kalamazoo, Mr. President.

395
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:26,590
-抱歉  总统女士  -没事的
- Excuse me, Madam President. - That's quite all right.

396
00:23:26,590 --> 00:23:28,310
我其实讨厌"女士"这个词
I actually hate "Madam."

397
00:23:28,310 --> 00:23:29,800
让我觉得自己是管理妓院的老鸨
Makes me sound like I'm running a brothel

398
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,110
不是在管理国家
and not a country.

399
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:33,410
-谢谢你的服役  -谢谢  总统女士
- Thank you for your service. - Thank you, Madam President.

400
00:23:33,410 --> 00:23:34,860
谢谢你的服役
Thank you for your service.

401
00:23:35,060 --> 00:23:36,880
你是哪来的  伯顿二等兵
And where are you from, Pvt. Burton?

402
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,300
南本德  女士
South Bend, ma'am.

403
00:23:38,790 --> 00:23:40,170
我爱印第安纳州
Oh, I love Indiana.

404
00:23:40,530 --> 00:23:42,570
我是在您上任前不久入伍的
I enlisted right before you took office.

405
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:45,400
我向你和美国所有女性保证
Well, I promise you and every woman in this country

406
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:47,100
在我任期内
that during my presidency

407
00:23:47,110 --> 00:23:49,740
会确保《平权修正案》的关键部分
the key components of the Equal Rights Amendment

408
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:51,280
终能获得通过
will finally pass.

409
00:23:51,450 --> 00:23:53,090
我会确保这一点的
I'm going to make sure of it.

410
00:23:53,730 --> 00:23:55,750
我希望你知道我支持你
I want you to know I support you.

411
00:23:56,550 --> 00:23:58,310
你制定好计划了吗
Do you even have a plan?

412
00:23:59,110 --> 00:24:00,260
你说什么
What did you say?

413
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:03,930
一个不会把我们都害死的计划
One that won't get us all killed?

414
00:24:04,290 --> 00:24:05,550
天呐
Oh, man...

415
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:09,110
如果我是个男人你还会这么问我吗
Would you have asked me that if I were a man?

416
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:19,900
总统女士
Madam President!

417
00:24:22,980 --> 00:24:24,500
请回答一个问题
One question, please!

418
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:11,230
{\an8}一个总统安葬另一个总统

419
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:14,400
试印

420
00:25:35,030 --> 00:25:37,130
我们还有多久能上飞机
How much longer till we get to the plane?

421
00:25:37,170 --> 00:25:39,680
还有25分钟左右  总统女士
Just another 25 minutes or so, Madam President.

422
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,140
好  谢谢
Okay, thank you.

423
00:25:41,990 --> 00:25:42,960
该死
Shit!

424
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:46,480
-她中枪了吗  -趴下  趴下
- Is she shot? - Stay down, stay down!

425
00:25:46,810 --> 00:25:49,010
有人开枪  有人开枪
Shots fired! Shots fired!

426
00:25:49,010 --> 00:25:50,340
你没事吧  总统女士
Are you okay, Madam President?

427
00:25:50,700 --> 00:25:52,240
-你没事吧  -没事
- Are you all right? - Yes.

428
00:25:53,020 --> 00:25:54,420
孤星安全
Lone Star is safe.

429
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:21,590
先生  刚有人企图行刺总统
Sir, someone just tried to kill the president.

430
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:24,810
我刚收到警报  她没事吧
I just got the alert. Is she all right?

431
00:26:25,570 --> 00:26:26,580
这边请
This way.

432
00:26:42,590 --> 00:26:43,650
林肯
Lincoln,

433
00:26:45,030 --> 00:26:46,800
加菲尔德  麦金利
Garfield, McKinley,

434
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,630
肯尼迪
Kennedy.

435
00:26:49,770 --> 00:26:52,370
刺杀成功  一共四起
Successful assassinations, total of four.

436
00:26:56,210 --> 00:26:59,060
企图刺杀  是九起吗
The attempts-- Nine?

437
00:27:00,180 --> 00:27:03,320
杰克逊  两个罗斯福
Jackson, both Roosevelts.

438
00:27:04,590 --> 00:27:06,830
特鲁门  福特两次
Truman. Ford twice.

439
00:27:07,470 --> 00:27:08,450
里根
Reagan...

440
00:27:09,860 --> 00:27:12,140
第一任安德伍德  还有...
the first Underwood and...

441
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:17,830
我得说  那个企图杀我的人
I will say, whoever tried to kill me,

442
00:27:18,250 --> 00:27:19,410
事与愿违了
perversely,

443
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:23,280
这是100天以来  我第一次真正感到受尊重
it's the first sign of real respect I've gotten in 100 days.

444
00:27:33,030 --> 00:27:34,550
有人企图杀她
Somebody tried to kill her.

445
00:27:36,700 --> 00:27:37,690
比尔
Bill.

446
00:27:40,230 --> 00:27:41,550
也难怪吧
Can you blame them?

447
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:46,000
安德伍德夫妇都挺耳背的
The Underwoods have always been hard of hearing.

448
00:27:47,090 --> 00:27:48,930
她不是他
She's not him.

449
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,310
是啊
No, no.

450
00:27:50,390 --> 00:27:51,760
她的确不是
She is not.

451
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:54,050
这你最清楚了
You know that better than anyone.

452
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,520
公开了吗
Is it public?

453
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:02,170
被特勤局保密了  据说是标准程序
Secret Service shut it down. Standard procedure, apparently.

454
00:28:02,170 --> 00:28:03,640
威胁会招致威胁
Threats beget threats.

455
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:06,370
比尔
Bill...

456
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,640
是你搞的吗
were you behind this?

457
00:28:12,350 --> 00:28:13,800
我们要错过烟火了
We're gonna miss the show.

458
00:28:22,340 --> 00:28:24,520
-你们好吗  -总统女士
- How are y'all? - Madam President.

459
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:25,450
真抱歉
Hi, I'm so sorry.

460
00:28:25,450 --> 00:28:27,750
我想为延迟出发表示道歉
I want to apologize for the late departure.

461
00:28:27,750 --> 00:28:30,770
我知道你们都还有家人和庆典在等着你们
I know you all have families and festivities waiting.

462
00:28:30,770 --> 00:28:34,550
总统女士  我可以问问发生了什么吗
Madam President, may I ask what happened?

463
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:38,300
因为安全原因  "野兽"总统专车改道了
The Beast was re-routed due to security concerns.

464
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:39,400
很正常的
It's pretty routine.

465
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:42,940
我知道我已经挺久没来过后面了
I know it's been a while since I've been back here.

466
00:28:42,940 --> 00:28:45,630
我想祝大家国庆节快乐
I just wanted to wish you all a very happy Fourth,

467
00:28:45,630 --> 00:28:48,670
虽然你们要明天才能庆祝了
even if you're gonna be celebrating it on the fifth.

468
00:28:48,670 --> 00:28:49,740
真抱歉
I'm so sorry.

469
00:28:49,740 --> 00:28:52,190
你的讲话  之后...
Your speech, afterwards with--

470
00:28:52,190 --> 00:28:54,100
是啊  那名新兵
Yes, the new recruit.

471
00:28:54,810 --> 00:28:57,050
如果一名新兵  尤其还是女兵
If a new recruit, especially a female one,

472
00:28:57,060 --> 00:28:58,390
不能表达自己的看法
can't speak her mind,

473
00:28:58,390 --> 00:29:01,890
那我真不知我们生活在什么样的国家里了
I don't know what kind of country we actually are.

474
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,950
如果你们没啤酒了一定要说
And be sure to tell us if you run out of beer.

475
00:29:07,950 --> 00:29:09,790
因为我敢肯定我们还有几箱
Because I am sure there's a couple of cases

476
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:11,940
是卡特政府时期留下的
left over from the Carter administration.

477
00:29:13,690 --> 00:29:15,280
你是新来的
And you're new.

478
00:29:16,160 --> 00:29:17,940
是的  女士  梅乐蒂·科鲁兹
Yes, ma'am. Melody Cruz.

479
00:29:17,940 --> 00:29:19,620
我是首都电视的
I'm with Beltway Television.

480
00:29:19,750 --> 00:29:21,920
希望大家对你还算热情
Well, I hope everyone is making you feel at home.

481
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,360
很热情
Very much so.

482
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:25,260
很荣幸终于见到了您
It's an honor to finally meet you.

483
00:29:25,750 --> 00:29:27,170
我有点激动了  抱歉
I'm a bit overwhelmed, sorry.

484
00:29:27,170 --> 00:29:29,850
-没事  我不咬人  -我知道
- Don't worry, I don't bite. - No, I know.

485
00:29:31,010 --> 00:29:34,770
很奇怪  我本该采访您丈夫的
It's strange, I was supposed to interview your husband.

486
00:29:35,700 --> 00:29:38,110
本来安排在他死后的几天
It was scheduled for a few days after he died.

487
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:40,700
本来会是一篇独家专访
It was going to be an exclusive.

488
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:42,770
我们已做了几次预采访
We'd had a number of pre-interviews.

489
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:44,800
也说定了一些问题
Questions we'd agreed on.

490
00:29:46,100 --> 00:29:47,270
什么样的问题
Questions like?

491
00:29:48,810 --> 00:29:51,960
比如  总统会赦免他吗
Like, was the president going to pardon him?

492
00:29:52,690 --> 00:29:53,760
以及何时
And when?

493
00:29:54,420 --> 00:29:56,890
你会吗  甚至是在他死后
Will you? Even now, posthumously?

494
00:30:00,070 --> 00:30:02,930
我知道你跟《纽约观察家》做了专访
I know you did an exclusive with The New York Examiner,

495
00:30:02,930 --> 00:30:06,940
但我猜那只会停留于表面
but I'm guessing that's only going to scratch the surface.

496
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,170
我相信你还有更多想说的
I bet you have more to say

497
00:30:09,740 --> 00:30:11,430
-关于你的婚姻状况  -小姐
- about the state of your marriage-- - Miss...

498
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:13,370
科鲁兹小姐  是吧
Cruz, is it?

499
00:30:13,660 --> 00:30:14,880
不知道有人跟你说过没有
I don't know if anyone's told you,

500
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:17,160
但总统来飞机这一区时
but when the president visits this part of the plane,

501
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:19,340
一般是默认为不做记录的
it's usually considered off the record.

502
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:21,580
但等我们落地了  你有什么问题
But you can ask my press secretary anything you like

503
00:30:21,580 --> 00:30:23,190
都可以问我的新闻发言人
once we're back on the ground.

504
00:30:33,570 --> 00:30:35,680
你今晚尤其地安静
You're especially quiet this evening.

505
00:30:37,070 --> 00:30:38,970
或许我有点焦躁
Maybe I'm a little agitated.

506
00:30:43,590 --> 00:30:46,700
我们的病人对烟火的反应都不佳
Our patients don't do too well when it comes to fireworks.

507
00:30:48,090 --> 00:30:49,090
抱歉
Pardon me.

508
00:30:56,220 --> 00:30:57,170
怎么了
Yes?

509
00:30:57,470 --> 00:31:00,230
我不明白我们会面时  你为什么还开着它
I don't understand why you leave that on when we're meeting.

510
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:04,350
反正你也不会说点什么新东西
Well, it's not like you're saying anything different or new.

511
00:31:04,710 --> 00:31:07,140
你照本宣科的执着都堪称可敬了
Your dedication to your script would be admirable

512
00:31:07,140 --> 00:31:09,180
只是这太让人担心
if it weren't so concerning.

513
00:31:12,330 --> 00:31:14,580
再过几周  我就要出席一场听证会
In a few weeks, I'll be appearing at a hearing

514
00:31:15,070 --> 00:31:17,060
就你的心理状态作证
regarding your state of mind

515
00:31:18,140 --> 00:31:20,490
至于你的供认
and when it comes to your confession,

516
00:31:20,700 --> 00:31:23,900
有罪之人也会时不时改变说辞
even a guilty man changes his story now and then.

517
00:31:27,870 --> 00:31:29,210
你听命于谁
Who do you answer to?

518
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:32,050
你为谁工作
I mean, who do you work for?

519
00:31:33,640 --> 00:31:34,660
你
You.

520
00:31:37,150 --> 00:31:38,820
至少该是这意思
That's the idea, anyway.

521
00:31:40,330 --> 00:31:42,260
每个人都有老板的
Everybody works for somebody.

522
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:51,080
我曾经的老板是一个不肯认输的人
I worked for a man who refused to fail.

523
00:31:53,190 --> 00:31:54,730
我尊重那点
I respected that.

524
00:31:55,760 --> 00:31:57,350
也很感激
I appreciated it.

525
00:32:02,710 --> 00:32:04,240
没有他我早死了
I'd be dead without him.

526
00:32:05,140 --> 00:32:06,120
为什么
Why?

527
00:32:17,340 --> 00:32:20,680
我原本是一个议员的助理
I was working as an aide for a congressman.

528
00:32:21,310 --> 00:32:23,160
他理想化又天真
He was idealistic and naive.

529
00:32:23,550 --> 00:32:25,750
一看就没有连任的命
Had one-term written all over him.

530
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:30,720
但我需要份工作  需要个去处
But I needed a job, a place to be.

531
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,970
我当时在勉强支撑
I was barely keeping it together.

532
00:32:37,930 --> 00:32:40,060
弗兰西斯和我在一场活动上相识
Francis and I met at some function.

533
00:32:40,890 --> 00:32:42,560
就是那种站着的活动
You know, the kind you stand up at.

534
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:49,970
我不知道他怎么知道的  但我车里有八瓶酒
I don't know how he knew, but I had eight bottles in my trunk.

535
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:53,640
那晚他找到我家时  我已经喝了四瓶
I got through four that night when he came to my door.

536
00:32:55,580 --> 00:32:56,980
我不记得多少了
I don't remember much.

537
00:32:58,140 --> 00:32:59,370
都很模糊了
Not clearly.

538
00:33:03,050 --> 00:33:04,440
他带我回了他家
He took me to his home.

539
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,330
但克莱尔...
But Claire...

540
00:33:11,060 --> 00:33:12,660
弗兰西斯帮我戒了酒
Francis got me dry.

541
00:33:14,930 --> 00:33:17,460
我抖得好厉害  我以为自己会死
I shook so badly I thought I was gonna die.

542
00:33:20,090 --> 00:33:22,360
等我终于戒掉了
And then when I was finally got clean,

543
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:24,530
他给了我第一份工作
he gave me my first job.

544
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:28,230
做助理吗
As an aide?

545
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:31,860
算是吧
Sort of.

546
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:36,210
他叫我去找爱荷华州的凯尔议员谈谈
He asked me to go talk to Congressman Kyle from Iowa.

547
00:33:36,810 --> 00:33:37,950
谈什么
To what end?

548
00:33:40,050 --> 00:33:41,200
说服他
To persuade him.

549
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,090
我做到了
And I did.

550
00:33:51,410 --> 00:33:52,460
但克莱尔...
But Claire...

551
00:33:54,340 --> 00:33:55,940
她对待他的方式
The way she treated him,

552
00:33:58,330 --> 00:33:59,990
不论是生前还是死后
in life and in death...

553
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:11,030
但为他那样的人工作总要付出代价
But you pay a price, when you work for somebody like him.

554
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:13,480
欠下人情债
Somebody you owe.

555
00:34:22,220 --> 00:34:24,720
我一个亲近的人死于了车祸
Somebody close to me died in a car accident.

556
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:30,470
所以我才违反了软禁协议
That's how I broke the terms of my house arrest.

557
00:34:33,420 --> 00:34:35,360
我去看她的车祸现场了
I went to see the site of her wreck.

558
00:34:37,060 --> 00:34:39,560
场面很难看  就在路边
It was twisted on the side of the road.

559
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,580
我站在那里
I just stood there.

560
00:34:46,420 --> 00:34:47,520
事故吗
An accident?

561
00:34:50,580 --> 00:34:51,660
他们说是的
So they said.

562
00:34:54,460 --> 00:34:55,930
佐伊·巴恩斯呢
And Zoe Barnes?

563
00:34:59,220 --> 00:35:00,290
我杀了她
I killed her.

564
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,650
为了总统
For the president.

565
00:35:14,820 --> 00:35:16,580
以前他赢了就会这么敲
That's what he used to do when he won.

566
00:35:20,420 --> 00:35:23,260
他给你留下了什么
What did he leave you with?

567
00:35:30,910 --> 00:35:33,240
弗兰西斯给我的最后一样东西
Last thing that Francis gave me was

568
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:35,310
是他桌上的拆信刀
the letter opener from his desk.

569
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:38,950
是我选的  但是
I mean, I chose it, but...

570
00:35:42,970 --> 00:35:45,850
或许该说他最后给我的一样东西  是一句道歉
But I guess really the last thing he gave me was an apology.

571
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:50,040
他死的那晚我跟他说过话
I spoke to him the night he died.

572
00:37:22,700 --> 00:37:25,540
我的任期将充满实干
My presidency will not rest.

573
00:37:25,250 --> 00:37:32,090
{\pos(189.3,184.8)}安德伍德总统独立日讲话

574
00:37:26,100 --> 00:37:28,300
南茜深深激励了我
Nancy has been an inspiration to me.

575
00:37:28,300 --> 00:37:29,810
她是不倦的勇士
A tireless warrior.

576
00:37:29,810 --> 00:37:31,560
我向她也向你们保证
I promise her and all of you

577
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:33,570
我会为我们的民主国家
that I will work on behalf of the rights

578
00:37:33,570 --> 00:37:37,800
这241年间所赢得的权利和自由而奋斗
and freedoms earned over the last 241 years of our democracy.

579
00:37:38,380 --> 00:37:40,320
暴君有多种多样
Tyrants come in many forms...

580
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,280
可悲
Pathetic.

581
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:44,290
从美国政治寡头企图改变
From the American oligarchs trying to change the very...

582
00:37:52,850 --> 00:37:55,880
你真不用休息一两个小时...
Are you sure you don't want to take an hour or two to--

583
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:58,310
马克  我在白宫呢
Mark. I'm inside the White House.

584
00:37:58,310 --> 00:38:00,940
总统办公室里只有你我  除非你带枪了
There's only two of us in the Oval, so unless you're packing,

585
00:38:00,950 --> 00:38:02,590
这对我真的是最安全的地方了
it's literally the safest place I can be.

586
00:38:02,610 --> 00:38:04,500
我没带枪  总统女士
Well, I'm not packing, Madam President,

587
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:07,660
但没人会怪你休息一会儿  喘口气的
but no one would fault you for taking a breath for a minute.

588
00:38:09,420 --> 00:38:11,030
我气喘得很匀
I'm breathing just fine.

589
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:14,830
我们能把这事保密吗
Can we keep news of this contained?

590
00:38:14,830 --> 00:38:16,690
我已经采取了一切可能措施
I've taken every possible step, I think.

591
00:38:16,690 --> 00:38:17,800
他是什么人
So who is he?

592
00:38:19,110 --> 00:38:22,230
他们在路上进行了采证
Well, they did forensics on the route.

593
00:38:22,230 --> 00:38:24,850
并与空中安保进行了沟通
Compared notes with the aerial detail.

594
00:38:25,350 --> 00:38:27,970
国土安全部和联调局都已介入
Homeland Secretary and the Bureau were brought in.

595
00:38:28,750 --> 00:38:32,260
他就没有离开他开枪的地方
He never left the place he took the shot from.

596
00:38:37,540 --> 00:38:40,730
你能直截了当地回答我吗
Can you answer a single question directly and simply?

597
00:38:43,390 --> 00:38:44,840
他一枪爆了自己的头
He shot himself in the head

598
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:47,950
用的是他自己的美军标准配发手枪
with his own US military-issued handgun.

599
00:38:50,170 --> 00:38:51,670
我们确定枪手就是他
And we're sure he's the one?

600
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:53,900
是  支持民兵组织  反政府
Yeah. Pro-militia. Anti-government.

601
00:38:54,490 --> 00:38:57,200
去年被开除军籍  有所有典型特征
Dishonorably discharged last year. All the typical markers.

602
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:58,880
特勤局确定是他
Secret Service is confident.

603
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:00,990
联调局也在调查了
And the Bureau's investigating.

604
00:39:04,340 --> 00:39:06,990
比尔·谢泼德怎么拿到我的讲话的
How did Bill Shepherd get his hands on my speech?

605
00:39:08,410 --> 00:39:09,320
什么
What?

606
00:39:09,660 --> 00:39:12,990
媒体往往几小时前就能拿到
Well, the press usually gets it hours before.

607
00:39:12,990 --> 00:39:15,450
想拿到一份应该不难吧
It wouldn't be that hard to access a copy, I guess.

608
00:39:18,700 --> 00:39:20,390
我今天不会签那个的
I won't be signing that today.

609
00:39:25,410 --> 00:39:27,010
你去那儿宣布你的独立
You went there to declare your independence,

610
00:39:27,010 --> 00:39:28,410
也宣了战
and you declared war.

611
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:29,380
那是个错误
That was a mistake.

612
00:39:29,380 --> 00:39:31,370
不  错误是我没雇幕僚长
No, the mistake was I didn't hire a chief of staff,

613
00:39:31,370 --> 00:39:32,770
就有些事疏于管理
and things are slipping through the cracks.

614
00:39:32,770 --> 00:39:34,020
这我就不能认同了
That's where I have to disagree with you.

615
00:39:34,020 --> 00:39:36,260
我们得保持一个小圈子
We need to keep this circle small.

616
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:39,620
弗兰西斯提醒过我小心你
You know, Francis warned me about you.

617
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:47,140
我向你保证  我为你效力  总统女士
I assure you, I serve at your pleasure, Madam President.

618
00:39:47,140 --> 00:39:50,220
你不能再在我的办公室里开不带我的会了
You need to stop meeting in my office without me.

619
00:39:54,010 --> 00:39:55,030
是  女士
Yes, ma'am.

620
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,380
是特勤局牵头调查的
Secret Service took the lead.

621
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:07,700
但你相信这个说法吗
But do you believe the theory?

622
00:40:07,700 --> 00:40:11,620
是一个不满的退役士兵冲我开了枪
That it was a disgruntled service person who took a shot at me?

623
00:40:11,740 --> 00:40:12,990
警方调查部认为是
PID does.

624
00:40:14,590 --> 00:40:16,230
我问你怎么想
I'm asking what you think.

625
00:40:20,050 --> 00:40:23,250
这要看这是警告还是真正的刺杀企图
It depends if it was a warning or an actual attempt.

626
00:40:24,170 --> 00:40:25,620
看他的准头
Given the accuracy,

627
00:40:25,620 --> 00:40:27,720
枪手应该有足够的情报知道
the shooter would have been informed enough to know

628
00:40:27,720 --> 00:40:30,770
.50子弹无法穿透"野兽"
that a .50 caliber round wouldn't penetrate the Beast.

629
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,990
我认为他就是想吓你
I think he wanted to scare you.

630
00:40:34,310 --> 00:40:35,950
替人办事
On behalf of someone.

631
00:40:35,950 --> 00:40:38,460
有很多人会对在任总统发出威胁
Lots of people make threats against sitting presidents.

632
00:40:38,460 --> 00:40:41,370
我开始认为弗兰西斯是被谋杀的
I'm starting to believe Francis was murdered.

633
00:40:45,950 --> 00:40:46,940
他死前
Before he died,

634
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:49,700
曾与一些很有势力的人结了盟
he aligned himself with some very powerful people.

635
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:51,690
我认为他们与他反目  并想杀死他
And I think they turned on him, and they wanted him dead,

636
00:40:51,690 --> 00:40:53,740
我觉得他们还想杀我
and I think they want me dead, too.

637
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:57,790
你觉得这听上去疯狂吗
Do you think that sounds crazy?

638
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:00,900
不  女士
No, ma'am.

639
00:41:01,670 --> 00:41:03,980
但我觉得我们该叫鲍曼特别探员来
But I think we need to bring in Special Agent Bowman--

640
00:41:03,980 --> 00:41:06,400
这些人  这些大家族
Of these people, these powerful families,

641
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:10,280
他们倡议解散情报机构
they advocate dismantling intelligence agencies.

642
00:41:10,290 --> 00:41:12,390
中情局  联调局  国土安全部
CIA, FBI, Homeland.

643
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:13,480
你知道吧
You know that, right?

644
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:15,380
-女士  -我们现在
- Ma'am-- - We cannot bring

645
00:41:15,530 --> 00:41:17,540
不能再拉上任何其他人
anyone else in at the moment.

646
00:41:19,080 --> 00:41:20,560
我指望你了
I'm relying on you

647
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:23,350
我知道我丈夫当初就能指望你
the way I know my husband could.

648
00:41:24,010 --> 00:41:25,840
请你去查查看
So, please see what you can find.

649
00:41:33,480 --> 00:41:34,820
你被称作过纳特吗
Is it ever Nate

650
00:41:35,210 --> 00:41:36,470
还是一直叫纳森
or always Nathan?

651
00:41:38,090 --> 00:41:39,110
纳森
Nathan.

652
00:41:40,860 --> 00:41:42,000
就像弗兰西斯
Like Francis.

653
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:43,660
至少我总那么叫他
For me, anyway.

654
00:41:48,720 --> 00:41:51,730
你跟道格·斯坦普谈过了吗
Oh, have you spoken to Doug Stamper?

655
00:41:54,430 --> 00:41:55,400
没有
No.

656
00:41:57,240 --> 00:41:58,750
我好担心他
I'm so worried about him.

657
00:41:58,750 --> 00:42:02,750
他做了令白宫每个人都不耻的事
He did things no one in this White House should be proud of.

658
00:42:26,580 --> 00:42:27,610
妈妈
Hey, Mom.

659
00:42:27,890 --> 00:42:29,730
你那边有多少人
How many people do you have there?

660
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:31,050
不多
Not many.

661
00:42:31,300 --> 00:42:33,280
至少没什么有趣的人
Nobody that interesting, anyway.

662
00:42:34,430 --> 00:42:35,920
她的基地之行
Her visit to the base.

663
00:42:36,330 --> 00:42:37,370
关于独立的讲话
Independence speech,

664
00:42:37,370 --> 00:42:39,910
甚至士兵的出言不逊对她都很有利
even the naughty soldier is playing well for her.

665
00:42:39,910 --> 00:42:42,670
她的魅力不减
Her charmed life persists.

666
00:42:43,020 --> 00:42:44,920
告诉比尔舅舅我们该加把劲
Tell Uncle Bill we should step up.

667
00:42:45,300 --> 00:42:47,990
我可以操纵舆论  削减她的魅力
I can manage the narrative. De-charm her.

668
00:42:47,990 --> 00:42:49,110
他不会喜欢那样的
He won't like that.

669
00:42:49,110 --> 00:42:50,290
反正这一切都不会让他高兴的
He's not going to like any of it,

670
00:42:50,290 --> 00:42:51,860
有什么区别呢
so what's the difference?

671
00:42:52,770 --> 00:42:56,060
-还是不好吧  -妈妈  就去说说吧
- I don't know. - Mom, just say the word.

672
00:42:58,180 --> 00:42:59,150
相信我
Trust me.

673
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:02,420
我回复你之前什么都别做
Don't do a thing until I get back to you.

674
00:43:22,580 --> 00:43:24,590
都看不出这里还是华府
Can't even tell you're still in DC.

675
00:43:25,580 --> 00:43:28,670
这座城市里有些地方永远都会是个秘密
There are parts of this city that will always remain a secret.

676
00:43:33,490 --> 00:43:34,570
顺说  我觉得我短期内
I don't think I'll be welcome back

677
00:43:34,580 --> 00:43:37,710
不会再被邀请加入白宫记者团了
in the White House press pool anytime soon, FYI.

678
00:43:38,290 --> 00:43:39,490
没关系
Doesn't matter.

679
00:43:41,430 --> 00:43:42,770
她不肯跟我谈
She won't speak to me.

680
00:43:42,980 --> 00:43:46,130
-采访不可能的  经过...  -她会答应的
- An interview? Not after-- - She will.

681
00:43:54,560 --> 00:43:56,960
今晚  他第一次主动开口
Tonight, for the first time, he was forthcoming.

682
00:43:57,130 --> 00:43:58,860
但还坚称他有罪
But still saying he's guilty?

683
00:43:58,860 --> 00:44:00,510
是的  一如既往
Yeah, as always.

684
00:44:01,350 --> 00:44:03,930
他提到格雷森先生的名字了吗
And did he mention Mr. Grayson by name?

685
00:44:03,930 --> 00:44:06,920
没有  他只是更难过了
No. He was just more distressed.

686
00:44:07,330 --> 00:44:08,660
他在恶化吗
So he's getting worse?

687
00:44:08,660 --> 00:44:10,720
也可能是好转  他可算开口了
Or better, he's finally talking.

688
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:16,310
但要说短期内让他离开那里
But the idea of his leaving the facility anytime soon,

689
00:44:16,730 --> 00:44:20,200
还是不可能的  这是为了他好
that's still out of the question. I mean, for his own good.

690
00:44:20,270 --> 00:44:21,800
他要么真犯了罪
He's either guilty of the crime

691
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:24,390
-要么认罪是在发疯  -总统女士
- or psychotic for admitting to it. - Madam President,

692
00:44:24,630 --> 00:44:26,500
谢泼德女士打到白宫来了
Miss Shepherd is on the White House line.

693
00:44:29,420 --> 00:44:32,410
或许该给他开抗精神病药了
Well, maybe it's time to give him one of the antipsychotics.

694
00:44:32,510 --> 00:44:36,130
或许吧  但我们得考虑他的瘾史
Possibly. But we'd have to consider his history of addiction.

695
00:44:37,110 --> 00:44:39,200
对了  回答你的问题
By the way, in answer to your question,

696
00:44:39,500 --> 00:44:41,010
是一把拆信刀
it was a letter opener,

697
00:44:41,230 --> 00:44:44,170
弗兰西斯从桌上拿来送他的最后一样东西
the last thing that Francis gave him from his desk.

698
00:44:44,390 --> 00:44:45,870
有情况再通知我  查尔斯
Keep me posted, Charles.

699
00:44:46,230 --> 00:44:47,500
谢谢你
And thank you.

700
00:44:48,260 --> 00:44:49,230
不客气
Sure.

701
00:44:55,590 --> 00:44:57,940
你准备好了吗
Are you prepared?

702
00:44:59,810 --> 00:45:00,850
什么
Excuse me.

703
00:45:02,550 --> 00:45:04,530
你不记得了吗  安多弗
Don't you remember? Andover?

704
00:45:04,530 --> 00:45:06,080
我们的预科学校玩笑
Our prep school joke?

705
00:45:07,720 --> 00:45:10,380
我准备当掉测试
I'm prepared to fail the test.

706
00:45:11,900 --> 00:45:13,140
你还好吗
Are you all right?

707
00:45:16,010 --> 00:45:20,600
抱歉这么晚打来  我听说了今天的事
I'm sorry to call so late. I-- I heard about what happened today.

708
00:45:23,280 --> 00:45:25,410
这些事总是不胫而走
These things have a tendency to leak out.

709
00:45:26,320 --> 00:45:27,480
我担心你
I'm worried about you.

710
00:45:28,230 --> 00:45:30,700
车队玻璃是防弹的
It's bulletproof, the motorcade glass.

711
00:45:30,750 --> 00:45:32,090
他们抓到那男人了吗
Did they catch the guy?

712
00:45:33,370 --> 00:45:34,930
你怎么知道是男人
How do you know it's a guy?

713
00:45:36,070 --> 00:45:37,780
总是男人嘛
It's always a guy, right?

714
00:45:43,190 --> 00:45:47,580
比尔希望修改我讲话的哪一部分
What was it Bill wanted adjusted in my speech?

715
00:45:51,300 --> 00:45:52,540
就是关于
Something about...

716
00:45:53,370 --> 00:45:54,410
自由的
freedom.

717
00:45:58,750 --> 00:46:00,450
我惦记着你  克莱尔
You're in my thoughts, Claire.

718
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:03,140
谢谢
Thank you.

719
00:46:04,120 --> 00:46:06,130
他还在我们身边  是吧
He's still with us, don't you think?

720
00:46:06,250 --> 00:46:07,210
谁
Who?

721
00:46:07,710 --> 00:46:08,770
弗兰克
Frank.

722
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:12,790
幸好他死前我们能跟他共度那么多的时光
We're so glad we got to spend so much time with him before he died.

723
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:17,110
他对我们说了些很有趣的事
He told us some fascinating things.

724
00:46:19,290 --> 00:46:20,690
我一直在想他
He's been on my mind.

725
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:27,310
比尔和我几天前总算去了趟加夫尼
Bill and I finally went down to Gaffney a few days ago...

726
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:31,500
